<br>
But then they go and let the lurikeens become heros, so that throws that out of the window.<br>
Unless you want to think of the &quot;moose&quot; form as a magical ability that fills that out somewhat, and think of Triple Wield as a non-magical &quot;Strength boost&quot; that increases our damage.<br>
<br>
It takes a lot of imagination stretching to do this.<br>
<br>
I think there was a very good reason that lurikeens weren't allowed to become heros, and they caved in to some of the RP players that didn't think through the behind-the-game stories that kept lurikeens from becoming heros to begin with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shermantank@lighttanksofdaoc>ShermanTank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Not Just a Blademaster -- a Siegemaster!</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#000000>(12/5/02 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why only celts and firbolgs?</span><hr size=1> the original idea was that lurks and elves come from beyond the vail and are &quot;magical&quot; celts and firbs stayed in the natral world and were &quot;nature&quot; thats why firbs and celts were the healers and fighters and elves and luris were the casters. the exeptions were Champ (magical fighters but firbs couldnt be them because they have NO magical ability) Ments (mind over mater caster their magic is more force of will than mystic) and the stealthers were in the magical department because they used magic for their abilities (the mid and alb spells and stealth were supposed to be tottaly different ways of achieveing the same effect)<br>
